tweet: Takeaways for athletes in all sports:  Success leads to sponsorship.  Have a business mindset.  Build a support team.  Capture content for yourself.  Create content for your sponsors.   Turn your followers into fans of  brand partners and you‚Äôll earn sponsorship $$ on the daily.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: Favorite takeaways for athletes in non-traditional sports:  Compete your ass off.  Join a sponsored team.  Branch out on your own.   1. Win enough, get free merch.  2. Win more, get cash incentives.  3. Keep winning and earn a salary from sponsors.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: But no matter the stage of the sponsorship journey, the athletes who retain deals (through ups and downs of competition) are those who invest in building their partner‚Äôs brand as well as their own.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: Once amateurs become elite and attract their own sponsors, they can get more selective with companies they partner with.   The shift in power dynamic ‚Äî from asking for sponsorship to turning sponsors away ‚Äî is the signal that one has ‚Äòmade it‚Äô.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: Once they‚Äôve caught the attention of brands beyond the sponsors on their team, some athletes will start to build a support team of their own.   There are marketing reps and agents for the most marketable athletes, and niche content creators are popping up in most sports.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: When athletes get serious about their sport, the goal is to earn a spot on a sponsored team.   This is often the first exposure to receiving free merchandise ‚Äî and their first relationship with a brand partner.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: The expert ambassadors establish their presence on YouTube, building up subscribers and viewership enough to make $1,000s per month from pre-roll advertising.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: Right below the elite athletes are the expert ambassadors.   These may not be the top performers, but they understand how to create content that captures an audience (and attracts brand partners).

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: The elites were once amateurs who picked up the sport as a hobby or a way to continue competition when they completed their college career.

name: Blake Lawrence üö™
tweet: In non-traditional sports, the top earners are elite athletes.   They‚Äôll have up to a dozen endemic (equipment, apparel, nutrition, etc.) brand partnerships ‚Äî receiving combo of free merch and some cash.
